    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-22T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-22T08:35:00-05:00" n="390"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/180: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-22T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >April 22, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 22—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Prime Minister was pleased when I conveyed to him the message contained in
                    first sentence of Department’s number 92.<note n="3" xml:id="d390fn3">Dated
                        April 15, 7 p.m., <ref target="#pg_334">p. 334</ref>.</note> He in turn
                    asked me to express to Department his appreciation of the heartening information
                    given by Department to Iranian Minister in Washington. He added that he would
                    much appreciate immediate permission to announce the extension of Lease-Lend aid
                    to Iran. A public statement to this effect he thought would not only strengthen
                    his political position but also would reassure certain elements in the Majlis
                    who are beginning to ask when and how the United States intends to assist Iran.
                    The specific questions raised in Department’s number 92 are being
                    investigated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
